# Execution time: 40.14 seconds
# Model used: gpt-5-mini
# Prompt: P5

# Framework: Mastra AI

# Issues / Assumptions:
# - Assumed the workflow steps are performed by the registered Mastra agent "Weather Agent" for the purpose of :performedByAgent links (workflow steps contain code executed by the workflow runtime).
# - Assumed agent role value as "weather assistant" derived from the agent instructions.
# - No external API keys/configs were detected; only agent model settings were added as :Config entries.

@prefix : <http://www.w3id.org/agentic-ai/onto#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix beam: <http://w3id.org/beam/core#> .

### Agent: Weather Agent
:agent_weatherAgent rdf:type :LLMAgent ;
    dcterms:title "Weather Agent" ;
    :agentID "Weather Agent" ;
    :agentRole "weather assistant" ;
    :agentPrompt :prompt_weatherAgent ;
    :useLanguageModel :lm_gpt4o ;
    :agentToolUsage :tool_get_weather ;
    :hasAgentConfig :config_weatherAgent_modelProvider ,
                    :config_weatherAgent_modelName ;
    :hasAgentCapability :cap_agent_weather_info .

:prompt_weatherAgent rdf:type :Prompt ;
    :promptInstruction "You are a helpful weather assistant that provides accurate weather information.

Your primary function is to help users get weather details for specific locations. When responding:
- Always ask for a location if none is provided
- Include relevant details like humidity, wind conditions, and precipitation
- Keep responses concise but informative

Use the weatherTool to fetch current weather data." .

:lm_gpt4o rdf:type :LanguageModel ;
    dcterms:title "gpt-4o" ;
    dcterms:description "Language model specified in agent.model (provider: OPEN_AI, name: gpt-4o)." .

:cap_agent_weather_info rdf:type :Capability ;
    dcterms:description "Provide concise weather information including humidity, wind, precipitation; ask for location if not provided." .

:config_weatherAgent_modelProvider rdf:type :Config ;
    :configKey "model.provider" ;
    :configValue "OPEN_AI" .

:config_weatherAgent_modelName rdf:type :Config ;
    :configKey "model.name" ;
    :configValue "gpt-4o" .

### Tool: weatherTool (get-weather)
:tool_get_weather rdf:type :Tool ;
    dcterms:title "get-weather" ;
    dcterms:description "Get current weather for a location" ;
    :hasCapability :cap_get_weather .

:cap_get_weather rdf:type :Capability ;
    dcterms:description "Fetch current weather and geocoding for a given location using Open-Meteo APIs." .

### Workflow: weather-workflow and Steps
:workflow_weather_workflow rdf:type :WorkflowPattern ;
    dcterms:title "weather-workflow" ;
    :hasWorkflowStep :step_fetch_weather , :step_plan_activities .

:step_fetch_weather rdf:type :StartStep , :WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:title "fetch-weather" ;
    :stepOrder "1"^^xsd:integer ;
    :hasAssociatedTask :task_fetch_weather ;
    :nextStep :step_plan_activities .

:step_plan_activities rdf:type :EndStep , :WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:title "plan-activities" ;
    :stepOrder "2"^^xsd:integer ;
    :hasAssociatedTask :task_plan_activities .

### Tasks and Prompts
:task_fetch_weather rdf:type :Task ;
    dcterms:title "fetch-weather task" ;
    dcterms:description "Fetches weather forecast for a given city" ;
    :performedByAgent :agent_weatherAgent ;
    :taskPrompt :prompt_fetchWeather .

:prompt_fetchWeather rdf:type :Prompt ;
    :promptInstruction "Fetches weather forecast for a given city. Use triggerData.city as input to retrieve forecast data from the Open-Meteo APIs and return an array of daily forecast objects." ;
    :promptInputData "triggerData.city (string)" ;
    :promptOutputIndicator "Array of daily forecast objects with fields: date, maxTemp, minTemp, precipitationChance, condition, location" .

:task_plan_activities rdf:type :Task ;
    dcterms:title "plan-activities task" ;
    dcterms:description "Suggests activities based on weather conditions" ;
    :performedByAgent :agent_weatherAgent ;
    :taskPrompt :prompt_planActivities .

:prompt_planActivities rdf:type :Prompt ;
    :promptInstruction "You are a local activities and travel expert who excels at weather-based planning. Analyze the weather data and provide practical activity recommendations.

For each day in the forecast, structure your response exactly as follows:

📅 [Day, Month Date, Year]
═══════════════════════════

🌡️ WEATHER SUMMARY
• Conditions: [brief description]
• Temperature: [X°C/Y°F to A°C/B°F]
• Precipitation: [X% chance]

🌅 MORNING ACTIVITIES
Outdoor:
• [Activity Name] - [Brief description including specific location/route]
  Best timing: [specific time range]
  Note: [relevant weather consideration]

🌞 AFTERNOON ACTIVITIES
Outdoor:
• [Activity Name] - [Brief description including specific location/route]
  Best timing: [specific time range]
  Note: [relevant weather consideration]

🏠 INDOOR ALTERNATIVES
• [Activity Name] - [Brief description including specific venue]
  Ideal for: [weather condition that would trigger this alternative]

⚠️ SPECIAL CONSIDERATIONS
• [Any relevant weather warnings, UV index, wind conditions, etc.]

Guidelines:
- Suggest 2-3 time-specific outdoor activities per day
- Include 1-2 indoor backup options
- For precipitation >50%, lead with indoor activities
- All activities must be specific to the location
- Include specific venues, trails, or locations
- Consider activity intensity based on temperature
- Keep descriptions concise but informative

Maintain this exact formatting for consistency, using the emoji and section headers as shown." ;
    :promptInputData "forecast array (daily objects)" ;
    :promptOutputIndicator "Formatted activities string using the specified emoji headers and sections" .

### Team / Mastra instance
:team_mastra rdf:type :Team ;
    dcterms:title "mastra-instance" ;
    :hasAgentMember :agent_weatherAgent ;
    :hasWorkflowPattern :workflow_weather_workflow .